Through this email request, I would like to obtain an updated PFAS Contamination Site Location Listing, for the entire United States, in Excel or other spreadsheet format. PFAS is a class of chemicals that includes PFOA (perfluorooctanoic acid), PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid), PFNA (perfluorononanoic acid) and PFHxA (perfluorohexanoic acid). PFOA and PFOS, are the most commonly found and potent PFASs at contamination sites. ATSDR is involved at a number of PFAS-related sites, either directly or through assisting state and federal partners. As of now, most sites are related to drinking water contamination connected with PFAS production facilities or fire training areas where aqueous film-forming firefighting foam (AFFF) was regularly used. We are working with one state partner on a site where consuming contaminated fish is the concern. Information I would like includes: Site name Location state Latitude Longitude If possible, I would also like: Contamination site name Location address Location city Location zip code Location county Name of source (s) Litigation (ues or no) PFOA or PFOS Other PFAS Date of discovery Suspected contamination source Suspected source url Notes Date Government response Community response Litigation details Agency site url

My request is for almost exactly the same dataset as is posted publicly online of the weekly provisional counts of deaths from any cause by age for the United States and by state: https://data.cdc.gov/NCHS/Weekly-counts-of-deaths-by-jurisdiction-and-age-gr/y5bj-9g5w/ This dataset is frequently updated on the CDC’s website; my request is for this same data, but instead of age breakdowns, it would include breakdowns by race/hispanic origin. Note that this request is a follow up to a previous such request, where the program directed me to data that I could use to extract monthly such counts. However that data is only updated until the end of 2018, and I require more recent data in order to capture the time period of the COVID-19 virus. The response also suggested I contact the NCHS Research Data Center (RDC), but indicated that this office is currently closed due to the pandemic, so this would not be feasible; additionally, since I am only requesting aggregate counts, it should not be necessary to make a research proposal to the RDC for restricted-use records of that kind. Therefore I’d like to ask for consideration of the fact that while the department’s previous response was approaching the data from my original request, it was ultimately not usable to me. Given this delay, I ask that the program give my current request attention as immediately as possible. As noted above, the data I’m seeking is very similar to other datasets that are currently publicly available and frequently updated online, including: 1) weekly provisional counts of deaths from any cause by age for the United States and by state, starting in 2015 and updated through May 2020, 2) weekly provisional counts of deaths involving COVID-19 by race and hispanic origin for the United States and by state, updated weekly, and 3) weekly provisional counts of all deaths for the United States and by state, starting in 2019 and updated through May 2020. If part of this request is denied for any reason, please detail the reason for the denial, and fulfill the remaining part of the request.
